1
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,120
Let me ask you.

2
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:56,900
Our Ms. Liu...

3
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:59,239
starred in the movie Flowers of the Motherland back then.

4
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:01,739
What year, month, and day did it premiere?

5
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,760
You even remember that?

6
00:02:05,739 --> 00:02:06,939
Even I've forgotten.

7
00:02:07,540 --> 00:02:08,599
I really don't know.

8
00:02:09,099 --> 00:02:10,039
Don't know, do you?

9
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:11,599
Let me ask you another one.

10
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:14,539
Back then, the movie Flowers of the Motherland...

11
00:02:14,620 --> 00:02:14,860
was at...

12
00:02:14,860 --> 00:02:15,539
Hold on a second.

13
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:18,439
You haven't told us the answer yet.

14
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,580
What was the exact year, month, and day?

15
00:02:20,759 --> 00:02:21,539
I'll tell you.

16
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,580
I don't know either.

17
00:02:23,699 --> 00:02:24,979
You don't know, yet you're quizzing us?

18
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:26,740
When did I say I knew?

19
00:02:28,740 --> 00:02:29,680
Let me test you then

20
00:02:30,819 --> 00:02:32,900
In the movie *Flowers of the Motherland*

21
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,879
Ms. Liu has a line

22
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:36,180
"Uncle"

23
00:02:36,439 --> 00:02:38,300
"When I grow up, I'll join the army"

24
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,479
What did the uncle say?

25
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:41,860
The uncle said

26
00:02:43,159 --> 00:02:44,939
"Little friend, you are very ambitious"

27
00:02:45,259 --> 00:02:45,840
Wrong

28
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:48,159
The uncle didn't answer

29
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,259
How is that possible?

30
00:02:51,460 --> 00:02:52,479
As an uncle

31
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,960
How could he be so rude?

32
00:02:54,039 --> 00:02:55,819
Because the scene cut to the next one

33
00:02:55,939 --> 00:02:56,919
Grandma Liu

34
00:02:57,580 --> 00:02:59,060
Hello Boss Li, Professor Fan

35
00:02:59,939 --> 00:03:01,000
Hello, Grandma Liu

36
00:03:01,419 --> 00:03:03,539
Thank you for giving us the acting lecture

37
00:03:03,659 --> 00:03:05,240
This is a gift from us

38
00:03:05,639 --> 00:03:06,800
Thank you

39
00:03:07,099 --> 00:03:07,979
What is this?

40
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:08,259
Yeah

41
00:03:08,259 --> 00:03:09,479
It's a Magic Bean

42
00:03:09,479 --> 00:03:11,000
It's very popular right now

43
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:12,740
Just open it

44
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:14,719
Water it a bit

45
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,240
And it will sprout in a few days

46
00:03:16,580 --> 00:03:17,860
On the leaves

47
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:19,319
Words will appear

48
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:19,919
These two

49
00:03:20,020 --> 00:03:21,300
One is a Career Bean

50
00:03:21,379 --> 00:03:22,759
One is called a Love Bean

51
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:23,419
It's really fun

52
00:03:23,419 --> 00:03:24,599
Amazing

53
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:25,000
It really is

54
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,379
That's wonderful

55
00:03:26,719 --> 00:03:27,479
I really

56
00:03:28,099 --> 00:03:28,939
Oh, I can't

57
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,479
I'm going traveling tomorrow

58
00:03:31,699 --> 00:03:32,620
I... I...

59
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:34,000
Leave that to me then

60
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,020
I'll grow it for you

61
00:03:35,159 --> 00:03:37,039
I'm the best at growing flowers and plants

62
00:03:37,099 --> 00:03:37,819
Wait a minute

63
00:03:38,699 --> 00:03:40,919
That succulent of yours the other day

64
00:03:40,919 --> 00:03:42,139
Didn't you kill it?

65
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:45,259
Such a drought-resistant desert plant

66
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,900
And you managed to kill it

67
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,919
You really are an expert

68
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:52,060
Is that so?

69
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:53,699
Then...

70
00:03:53,939 --> 00:03:54,919
Let me do it

71
00:03:55,439 --> 00:03:57,159
I'm someone who has actually grown crops

72
00:03:57,259 --> 00:03:59,180
And raised farm produce

73
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,379
You

74
00:04:00,460 --> 00:04:01,580
You grew crops?

75
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:03,620
Then why did you trick me

76
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:06,280
Into watering a desert plant non-stop?

77
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:08,539
As soon as I see this Magic Bean

78
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:10,240
I think of my succulent

79
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,560
It died so miserably

80
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:14,520
Is that

81
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,639
How you raise crops?

82
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:17,139
No, well...

83
00:04:17,139 --> 00:04:17,639
Well...

84
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:18,540
No, it's just...

85
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,500
If Old Li...

86
00:04:20,879 --> 00:04:22,120
As long as he doesn't interfere

87
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,720
I will definitely take care of this Magic Bean personally

88
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:25,879
I promise

89
00:04:25,879 --> 00:04:27,800
Like I cherish my own eyes

90
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:29,379
I will cherish it

91
00:04:29,459 --> 00:04:30,740
That would be bad

92
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:32,040
Look at how he

93
00:04:32,079 --> 00:04:33,699
Cherishes his own eyes

94
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:36,259
Reading, writing, staring at the computer

95
00:04:36,779 --> 00:04:38,480
He literally ruined his eyes

96
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,339
Into severe nearsightedness

97
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,600
You'd better give it to me

98
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:42,759
Give it to me

99
00:04:42,980 --> 00:04:43,379
Give it to me

100
00:04:43,379 --> 00:04:43,720
Alright

101
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:43,980
Grandpas

102
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:45,120
I can definitely grow it well

103
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,160
Let's not argue

104
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,759
I actually have a good idea

105
00:04:47,839 --> 00:04:48,699
If you ask me

106
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:50,000
You two

107
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:51,740
Take one each

108
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,439
See

109
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,160
Who can make the words appear first

110
00:04:55,579 --> 00:04:56,100
Good

111
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,240
One box of love

112
00:05:01,319 --> 00:05:01,720
Yes

113
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:02,500
One box of career

114
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:02,939
Right

115
00:05:03,079 --> 00:05:04,220
Which box is career?

116
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,480
And which box is love?

117
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,360
You don't know, do you?

118
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,600
Let me tell you

119
00:05:09,079 --> 00:05:10,019
I don't know either

120
00:05:10,319 --> 00:05:11,319
Nonsense again

121
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:12,839
But I have a way to find out

122
00:05:12,899 --> 00:05:13,680
What way?

123
00:05:14,579 --> 00:05:15,740
Wait for words to grow on it

124
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:16,920
That's like saying nothing

125
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,220
Old Li

126
00:05:18,439 --> 00:05:19,519
You don't understand this

127
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,120
The words on these leaves

128
00:05:22,660 --> 00:05:24,079
don't appear all at once

129
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:25,980
They come out bit by bit

130
00:05:26,279 --> 00:05:27,620
At first, you have to guess

131
00:05:28,379 --> 00:05:28,879
How about this

132
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:29,779
The two of us

133
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,959
let's each claim one first

134
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,259
How about we raise them together?

135
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,139
Nurture a seed of love together

136
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:36,660
Ridiculous

137
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,660
So you mean we raise them separately

138
00:05:38,759 --> 00:05:39,120
Yes

139
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:40,860
The key point

140
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:42,560
isn't about what words grow

141
00:05:42,819 --> 00:05:44,959
it's about whether words will grow at all

142
00:05:45,819 --> 00:05:46,879
That makes sense

143
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:48,980
If

144
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,120
your bean dies

145
00:05:51,279 --> 00:05:52,819
and my bean grows words

146
00:05:52,899 --> 00:05:54,720
then no matter the word, I'm the winner

147
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,860
We don't know whose bean will die first yet

148
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,420
Then let's have a contest

149
00:06:00,839 --> 00:06:01,439
You're on

150
00:06:05,199 --> 00:06:05,839
Xiaoxin

151
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:07,019
You got a new phone?

152
00:06:08,019 --> 00:06:09,459
My boyfriend bought it for me

153
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,660
Your boyfriend treats you pretty well

154
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:14,079
It's true love between us

155
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:16,420
Then do you dare to test him?

156
00:06:17,019 --> 00:06:18,180
Test him how?

157
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:19,220
Like this

158
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,939
Say you lost your phone

159
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,579
Ask him to buy you another one

160
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:25,139
See if his love for you is worth two phones

161
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:27,379
What do I need two phones for?

162
00:06:27,459 --> 00:06:28,480
Give one to me

163
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,879
I've been wanting a new phone recently

164
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,220
Don't tell me our Xiaoxin

165
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,439
is only worth two phones?

166
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:35,339
At least three

167
00:06:36,139 --> 00:06:37,240
I want a new phone too

168
00:06:37,879 --> 00:06:39,639
Her boyfriend isn't short of three phones

169
00:06:39,639 --> 00:06:41,100
As long as our Xiaoxin asks

170
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,259
one for each of us

171
00:06:42,519 --> 00:06:43,160
Xiaoxin

172
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,019
Try it

173
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:45,279
Why should I?

174
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,279
Am I stupid?

175
00:06:46,339 --> 00:06:47,680
You're not stupid

176
00:06:47,779 --> 00:06:49,040
Your taste is just a bit poor

177
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:51,480
Her taste isn't poor

178
00:06:51,819 --> 00:06:53,300
She just has a good heart

179
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:53,879
Right

180
00:06:53,959 --> 00:06:55,879
If you help, help the classmates in most need

181
00:06:55,939 --> 00:06:57,079
If we're talking need

182
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,220
who's more in need than you two?

183
00:06:58,279 --> 00:06:59,019
Xiaoxin

184
00:06:59,259 --> 00:07:00,279
Don't listen to them

185
00:07:00,319 --> 00:07:02,120
I think your boyfriend is quite nice

186
00:07:02,319 --> 00:07:04,060
Down-to-earth and low-key

187
00:07:04,139 --> 00:07:05,439
Faithful and obedient

188
00:07:05,459 --> 00:07:06,019
Right

189
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:07,800
We just like that he's dumb

190
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,000
That he's a good person

191
00:09:36,539 --> 00:09:37,500
Can't sleep.

192
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:40,299
Might as well read a book.

193
00:09:42,379 --> 00:09:44,120
It is now...

194
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:45,740
three o'clock.

195
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:49,320
Read until six in the morning.

196
00:09:50,379 --> 00:09:51,779
Then exercise.

197
00:09:52,639 --> 00:09:54,120
Then breakfast.

198
00:09:54,659 --> 00:09:56,000
Then sleep a bit more.

199
00:09:57,519 --> 00:09:59,320
Reading in bed...

200
00:09:59,980 --> 00:10:01,759
for three hours is so comfortable.

201
00:10:02,919 --> 00:10:05,139
But lying on the floor for three hours...

202
00:10:05,139 --> 00:10:06,200
can't be comfortable.

203
00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:08,919
Can you still get up?

204
00:10:10,279 --> 00:10:12,000
Don't catch a cold now.

205
00:10:16,580 --> 00:10:17,519
Professor Fan.

206
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:19,779
What are you doing?

207
00:10:20,159 --> 00:10:21,360
What kind of kung fu are you practicing?

208
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:22,679
No...

209
00:10:23,299 --> 00:10:23,840
I...

210
00:10:24,159 --> 00:10:24,820
I am...

211
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,779
My sleepwalking habit is acting up again.

212
00:10:26,779 --> 00:10:27,539
Sorry about that.

213
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:28,299
It's fine.

214
00:10:28,659 --> 00:10:29,539
As long as you're happy.

215
00:10:29,919 --> 00:10:31,220
You can roam under my bed all you want.

216
00:10:31,919 --> 00:10:32,840
You can lie there as long as you like.

217
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:34,480
Alright.

218
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:35,879
I admit it.

219
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:36,879
I wanted to...

220
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,919
see how your Magic Beans are growing.

221
00:10:39,019 --> 00:10:40,139
You're welcome to look at the Magic Beans too.

222
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,240
If I had known...

223
00:10:42,419 --> 00:10:44,679
I would have put the Magic Beans under my bed.

224
00:10:44,759 --> 00:10:45,820
That way, while you're lying there...

225
00:10:45,860 --> 00:10:46,639
you could watch them.

226
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:48,159
Go back to sleep.

227
00:10:49,019 --> 00:10:50,000
I'm going back now.

228
00:10:51,019 --> 00:10:52,100
Won't lie there a bit longer?

229
00:11:01,740 --> 00:11:02,460
Students.

230
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:04,340
I just want to ask...

231
00:11:04,399 --> 00:11:06,120
those two Magic Beans you bought...

232
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:08,059
which one is the Love Bean...

233
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:09,120
and which one is the Career Bean?

234
00:11:09,659 --> 00:11:10,399
Professor Fan.

235
00:11:10,399 --> 00:11:11,679
Is that all you wanted to ask?

236
00:11:12,379 --> 00:11:13,320
I don't know either.

237
00:11:15,139 --> 00:11:16,580
Then when you bought them...

238
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,279
how did you know there were two types?

239
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:19,919
There was packaging.

240
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,039
It was written on the packaging.

241
00:11:21,039 --> 00:11:21,799
Wait a moment.

242
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,580
This one is the Love Bean.

243
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:27,759
This one is the Career Bean.

244
00:11:27,799 --> 00:11:29,460
Great, I'll take the Love Bean.

245
00:11:29,759 --> 00:11:30,600
No, wait.

246
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,460
These two pieces of paper...

247
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:34,179
which one wrapped which?

248
00:11:34,740 --> 00:11:35,279
I forgot.

249
00:11:36,220 --> 00:11:37,240
I remember now.

250
00:11:37,519 --> 00:11:39,399
The young lady selling the Magic Beans...

251
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:40,919
looked at the bottom of the box.

252
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,279
Maybe there's a mark on the bottom of the box.

253
00:11:43,740 --> 00:11:44,980
Professor Fan, do you thi...

254
00:11:45,679 --> 00:11:46,399
Professor Fan.

255
00:11:46,779 --> 00:11:47,600
Professor Fan.

256
00:11:53,179 --> 00:11:53,899
Old Li.

257
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:55,019
Why are you back?

258
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,580
I'm entering my own room.

259
00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:57,460
Without knocking?

260
00:11:58,019 --> 00:11:59,200
What are you doing sneaking around?

261
00:11:59,639 --> 00:12:00,740
Do I need to come in again?

262
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,480
Enough, Old Li.

263
00:12:02,580 --> 00:12:03,379
What are you doing?

264
00:12:03,679 --> 00:12:05,519
I just wanted to look at your Magic Bean box.

265
00:12:05,519 --> 00:12:06,720
Do you have to be so stingy?

266
00:12:07,179 --> 00:12:09,580
You were clearly plotting against my Magic Bean box.

267
00:12:09,779 --> 00:12:11,120
And I caught you red-handed.

268
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:12,840
And you act like the victim.

269
00:12:13,519 --> 00:12:14,980
Who's plotting?

270
00:12:15,519 --> 00:12:16,840
Who did you catch red-handed?

271
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:17,659
Then what were you doing?

272
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,799
You lack curiosity.

273
00:12:18,799 --> 00:12:19,740
You have no ambition.

274
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,840
Have you never thought...

275
00:12:21,940 --> 00:12:23,840
to study these two Magic Bean boxes?

276
00:12:24,259 --> 00:12:25,080
Study what?

277
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,220
Don't you want to know...

278
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:27,159
which one is the Love Bean...

279
00:12:27,159 --> 00:12:28,200
and which one is the Career Bean?

280
00:12:28,559 --> 00:12:29,659
I couldn't care less.

281
00:12:31,779 --> 00:12:32,500
Which one?

282
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:34,980
You tell me which is which.

283
00:12:35,019 --> 00:12:36,279
Do you want me to tell you?

284
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:39,940
Tell me or don't.

285
00:12:40,679 --> 00:12:41,720
If not, forget it.

286
00:12:41,860 --> 00:12:42,840
You have to beg me.

287
00:12:43,019 --> 00:12:44,440
Why should I tell you if you don't beg me?

288
00:12:51,399 --> 00:12:52,620
I beg you

289
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,799
You're begging me?

290
00:12:54,379 --> 00:12:55,659
Shouldn't you apologize first?

291
00:12:55,659 --> 00:12:57,100
I apologize

292
00:12:57,340 --> 00:12:59,179
Is this attitude sincere?

293
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:00,820
If you don't tell me, forget it

294
00:13:01,059 --> 00:13:02,139
Fine, I'll tell you

295
